WebtrisulDashboard.name: TCP Analyzer
WebtrisulDashboard.description: Analysis of TCP activity like Retransmission, Latency etc.

WebtrisulDashboard.name: Internal Hosts: Setup Latency  (us)
WebtrisulDashboard.description: Latency of connection setup, completion of 3-way handshake for Internal Hosts. Click on any host for a drilldown

WebtrisulDashboard.name: Internal Hosts: Retransmitted Packets
WebtrisulDashboard.description: Top Internal Hosts with most number of absolute retransmitted packets.

WebtrisulDashboard.name: Internal Hosts: Avg Retransmit Rate Percent
WebtrisulDashboard.description:
Internal hosts with high retransmission rate averaged across all flows. 
Retransmitted packets as a percentage of total packets. Anything above 2-5% is poor.

WebtrisulDashboard.name: High Retransmit >5% Flows
WebtrisulDashboard.description: Count of flows experiencing a higher than 5% retransmission rate.   Note that this is NOT the average retransmit rate per Host but the absolute number of Flows with > 5% retrans rate.

WebtrisulDashboard.name: External Hosts : Setup Latency (us)
WebtrisulDashboard.description: Latency of connection setup, completion of 3-way handshake for External  Hosts.  Units : Microseconds

WebtrisulDashboard.name: External Hosts: Retransmitted Packets
WebtrisulDashboard.description: Top External Hosts with most number of retransmitted packets. Click on item to explore further.

WebtrisulDashboard.name: External Hosts: Avg Retransmit Rate Percent
WebtrisulDashboard.description:
Top External Hosts with High Retransmit Rate <strong>AVERAGED</strong> across all flows for that host.

Retransmit packet count as a percentage of total packet count

WebtrisulDashboard.name: Number of flows Timed Out
WebtrisulDashboard.description:
Per Host 
Number of Flows that Timed OUT rather than go through a normal FIN or RST based TCP connection close protocol.

WebtrisulDashboard.name: Flows with > 5% retransmit rate
WebtrisulDashboard.description: List of individual flows with greater than 5% retransmit rate. The flows are sorted in order of Highest Retransmit Rate first. You can pull the packets into Wireshark or Unsniff from this list for further analysis.
